<plot>Two siblings, Sandro and Sofiko, leave behind materialistic aspirations of their peers to plunge into the exciting world of self-discovery. The film merges the worlds of theater and marine biology into a burlesque atmosphere of wild creativity. It is a film-fantasy, a film-spectacle, where visual structure takes precedence over conventional storytelling. Influenced by the films of Otar Iosseliani, the objective of Moment Theatral is to convey emotions using the unique expressive possibilities of the language of cinema.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?374804</url></doc>
